            "description": "This is a special issue that I co-edited with Jesse Ovadia to be published in Third World Quarterly examining the political conditions, elite strategies, and policy innovations in building developmental states in countries with less capacity as their East Asian counterparts. We survey a range of countries, including Argentina, Ethiopia, and China, as well as sectoral approaches to capacity-building, notably in extractive industries and traditional manufacturing, to explore how states manage economic globalization through the logic of developmentalism.",
